        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(android): localize native app locale matrix",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nThe Android Node app had only English, Russian, and Hindi resources, and its parity check was hard-coded to those two translations.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nMove the gateway connection/onboarding strings onto Android resources for the complete shared native locale matrix. Android qualifiers are generated correctly for regional locales such as `zh-rCN`, `zh-rTW`, `pt-rBR`, and `ja`.\n\n## User Impact\n\nThe Android gateway setup surface now has complete English plus 20 translated resource directories. The checker derives its locale list from the shared native inventory contract, so new matrix additions fail closed instead of silently falling back.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- `node --import tsx scripts/android-app-i18n.ts check`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs test/scripts/android-app-i18n.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check`\n\nAndroid Gradle lint/build remains environment-dependent because this checkout does not have an Android SDK configured. This PR is stacked on #97110.",
